1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
2 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
3 HOUSE BILL 3652 By: Stinson
4
5
6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to courts; defining term; providing
for codification; and providing an effective date.
8
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
11 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
12 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 121.3 of Title 20, unless there
13 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
14 For purposes of Section 129 of Title 20 of the Oklahoma
15 Statutes, the term "municipal judge" shall mean any full-time judge
16 presiding over a court of record in the State of Oklahoma who is not
17 practicing law as a licensed attorney.
18 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
